<body>
    <div class="navbar">Device Restrictions in Intune</div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Application Restrictions</h2>
            <p>Control which apps can be installed or used on the device.</p>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Go to Intune Admin Center.</li>
                <li>Navigate to **Device Configuration** → **Profiles**.</li>
                <li>Create a **Device Restriction Profile**.</li>
                <li>Configure app restrictions and assign to users or devices.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Hardware Restrictions</h2>
            <p>Limit the use of device features like camera, USB, or Bluetooth.</p>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Go to **Endpoint Security** → **Device Restrictions**.</li>
                <li>Select the restrictions to apply (e.g., disable camera).</li>
                <li>Assign the policy to device groups.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Network Restrictions</h2>
            <p>Restrict access to specific networks or enforce VPN usage.</p>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Go to **Intune Admin Center**.</li>
                <li>Navigate to **Device Configuration** → **Profiles**.</li>
                <li>Create a new **Wi-Fi or VPN restriction policy**.</li>
                <li>Assign it to the required devices.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
